  "text": "The cerebellar posterior hemisphere, which showed aberrant FCs with cerebral cortices, is involved in a variety of cognitive functions. The Crus I/II are involved in language processing and executive function [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Although the functional role of the lobule IX remains unclear, it might be involved in social cognition by cooperation with the default mode network in the cerebral regions [CITATION_3] . We found decreased FC between the lobule IX and lobule VI, and this was correlated with poorer socio-communicative function in the ASD group. Since the lobule VI is involved in language processing [CITATION_4] , the results of our correlation analysis are consistent with the functional role of the lobule IX.",
